ACH payments are electronic payments made through the Automated Clearing House (ACH) network in the United States. In Acumatica ERP, you can automate payments to vendors by making ACH payments. To do this, you export a batch of payments to a file that is then processed in the ACH system. For each vendor, the specified amount is automatically credited from one of your company&rsquo;s bank accounts and transferred to the payment recipient electronically. {br}

The National Automated Clearing House Association (NACHA) has developed the rules and standards about ACH transactions, including the following:[anchor|#ul_ywj_sb3_rp]
*To set up ACH payments, you need an agreement and an account with the ACH operator—that is, the financial institution providing ACH services. 
*You need agreements with your vendors covering ACH transaction authorization, and information about their accounts in the ACH network. Accounts are identified by the financial institution&rsquo;s routing number and the account number within that institution.

By using ACH payments, you reduce errors, while eliminating the hassles of check preparation, printing, and emailing. Because you can pay promptly, you also can usually get available cash discounts. {br}{TOC}
==Setup of Payment Processing==
To start paying your vendors through the ACH network, you should perform the following steps:[anchor|#ol_tfp_lcn_pp]
#You sign up for the ACH service with the ACH operator. As part of the sign-up process, you receive the credentials with which your company is registered in the ACH network, such as account number, bank routing number, and company identification.
#You set up agreements with your vendors covering ACH transaction authorization, and you get information about their accounts in the ACH network.
#You set up the payment method to be used for ACH payments. The payment method includes elements that need to be filled with the vendor&rsquo;s custom information, file export details, and details that need to filled with your ACH credentials. For details, see [HelpRoot_Integration\CA__HOW_Add_PM_for_ACH|To Add a Payment Method for ACH Payments]. 
#You specify remittance information (ACH credentials) for each cash account you are going to use as a source for paying your vendors. For details, see [HelpRoot_Integration\CA__HOW_Add_RemittanceInfo_to_CashAccount|To Add Remittance Information to a Cash Account].
#You assign the payment method intended for ACH payments to each vendor that will accept ACH payments. By using the ACH-related information you collected from each vendor in Step 2, fill in the settings of the payment method on the '''Payment Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form. 

==Implementation Details==
The ACH system supports the processing of ''balanced'' and ''unbalanced'' files. A balanced file contains an offsetting entry that automatically credits or debits the specified offset account for the debit or credit transactions in the file. An unbalanced file contains only the transactions you specify and does not include an offsetting entry.{br}

 Acumatica ERP provides functionality you can use to export payments to get a balanced or unbalanced file. You export payments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_70_25|Export Scenarios] ([~/?ScreenId=SM207025|SM207025]) form by using a scenario designed for the ACH payment method. The export scenarios ''Export AP Payments to ACH'' and ''Export AP Payments to ACH Balanced'', which were developed for the corporate credit or debit (CCD) application of the ACH system, fully complies with the file format specifications for ACH. The result of exporting payments is a file that is then processed in the ACH system. {br}

The export scenarios ''Export AP Payments to ACH'' and ''Export AP Payments to ACH Balanced'' (which are provided with Acumatica ERP) create unbalanced and balanced files respectively that are then processed in the ACH system. {br}

Also, you can modify the scenario if another ACH application will be used or if your financial institution uses another format for electronic funds transfer. {br}

The ''Export AP Payments to ACH'' scenario uses the <tt>ACHExportProvider</tt> data provider and the ''Export AP Payments to ACH Balanced'' one uses <tt>ACHBalancedProvider</tt>. ((({S:Warn}
Do not delete the <tt>ACHExportProvider</tt> or <tt>ACHBalancedProvider</tt> data providers. If you have accidentally deleted it, contact Acumatica ERP support to restore it.
))){br}

The export scenario is configured to use exact identifiers of payment method details as those defined for payment method details in the ''FEDWIRE'' and ''FEDWIREBA'' demo payment methods. If you add details to your payment method manually, either copy identifiers from the demo payment method or adjust the scenario accordingly. For details, see [HelpRoot_Integration\CA__HOW_Add_PM_for_ACH|To Add a Payment Method for ACH Payments].

You use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_40_00|Payment Methods] ([~/?ScreenId=CA204000|CA204000]) form to create a payment method to be used for Automated Clearing House (ACH) payments in one of the following ways:[anchor|#ul_s5l_2qn_pp] *By using the ''FEDWIRE'' (exports payments to unbalanced file) and ''FEDWIREBA'' (exports payments to balanced file) payment methods, which are preconfigured and available for selection on this form. ''FEDWIRE'' and ''FEDWIREBA'' are already configured to be used for paying your vendors through the ACH network. *By using the ''FEDWIRE'' or ''FEDWIREBA'' payment method as a basis and using commands on the '''Clipboard''' menu on the form toolbar. You can copy the settings of a particular payment method and paste them to create another one (changing any needed settings), or you can create a template for multiple similar payment methods. For details, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM__con_Copy-and-Paste_Options_and_Document_Templates|Copy-and-Paste Options and Document Templates]. *By entering the settings of a payment method manually. {br}
